title: Emscripten builds broken on nightly? (Linking errors in fresh "hello world" crate)

labels.name: A-linkage
labels.description: Area: linking into static, shared libraries and binaries

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: regression-from-stable-to-stable
labels.description: Performance or correctness regression from one stable version to another.

labels.name: E-needs-mcve
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue needs a Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example

body:
I have the current nightly (did rustup update today), current cargo-web (0.6.26), and if I do `cargo new` followed by `cargo web start --target=wasm32-unknown-emscripten`, I get linking errors.

Same error occurs on nightly-2019-11-25. Also occurs when the target is asmjs-unknown-emscripten. The build succeeds on stable (1.39.0), and succeeds on nightly when the target is wasm32-unknown-unknown.
